list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Data Analytics: - Graph program that takes a module code and email address. - Runs through the database checking if the user has attended that class, enumerates a list. - Once all classes have been checked, creates a bar chart and emails the specified email the data. - Commented code

task.summary:
Updated Code: - Database Complete Rewrite - SQL Statements rewrite - Export database attendance table to PDF and email to lecturer's email - ++ lots more
TBA: - Temp attendance database - Redesign GUI

Updated Code: - Menu bar with options (select room, student mode, about, credits, quit) - Select room (allows to set up what room the device should check classes from - Student mode (removes menu bar and window title, press ESC to revert) - About TBA - Credits (credits) - Quit (exits the program and closes all threads running)
TBA: - Message boxes need to be redone to allow for pop up windows - Temp class room rather than new class every time - ++ more

Updated Code: - Database now has Room Temp tables that pull in the current class user information. Temp table gets copied to ModuleCode.ModuleCode_Timestamp in the database. Temp room table clears when class is finished, ready for new class information.
TBA: Fix export PDF so it exports the newly copied and created table rather than the temp class table.

Updated Code: - Continued work on the GUI. I'd say it's now basically finished, with maybe minor touches to the GUI as required. - Decided to instead of doing message boxes over the videoStream to provide a on-screen keyboard that the user can input the room numbers into. - This can further be expanded to include a keyboard with certain letters if necessary. However, it's out of scope at this stage.
TBA: - Populate the database with Lecturers + Students, their faces and a populate rest of database, including more modules and classes.
Before "The big test": - Optimize code, this includes checking all of the threads work / close when needed. This will speed up the program. - Will also export out of One Drive before running for best performance. - Clean up print statements in cmd line as well before the test. - Comment all new code!
"The big test": - Run a day simulation to see how well the code performs. (can record screen throughout for video)
Analytics (?): - Will look into doing something with the data from the SQL when I have time, could be interesting to add this into our technical report! (bonus marks) - Might use matpotlib to create a secondary smaller program that can extract the sql data, convert to visual representations and email to lecturers.

Updated Code: - Fixed threads so they not work in parallel, and the class database gets updated before class is finished. This is so the program has time to re-initialize class checking. (set to 15 seconds before at the momment)
TBA: - Re-skin the module code pop up window. - Comment code - Remove redundant code - Start to populate DB

Updated Code: - Re-skinned the module code pop up window - Commented all the code
TBA: - Start to populate DB

Updated Code: - Fixed a bug where the output path wasn't updating when a new class was found - Fixed a bug where the export list wasn't clearing before exporting, resulting in all users being added to it.
TBA: - Start populating the database for "the big test"
Updated Code: - Fixed email body to not contain folder path - Removed completed TODO lists

Populated database: http://cbcl.mit.edu/software-datasets/heisele/facerecognition-database.html
Used MIT face recognition database to produce ten new students, populated the database with 5 modules, a room schedule and new lecturers. (For testing purposes only using one email to export)
Updated Code: - Fixed bug - Reset lateTimer, attendees list, late_attendees list when exporting current class.
Updated Code: - Fixed bug where PDF headers were getting added incorrectly to the very first pdf export. This has been resolved by appending the headers to the list inside the exportToPDF function
Updated Packages: - Fixed a bug that I didn't realise, I was using a different venv folder to the one in this directory. Therefore, project couldn't run if downloaded!

Data Analytics: - Graph program that takes a module code and email address. - Runs through the database checking if the user has attended that class, enumerates a list. - Once all classes have been checked, creates a bar chart and emails the specified email the data. - Commented code
